==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{SAMPA|/"si:m@n/}}

====Homophones====
*[[seamen]], [[semen]]

===Noun===
'''seaman''' (''plural:'' '''seamen''')

#One whose occupation is to assist in the management of ships at [[sea]]; a [[mariner]]; a [[sailor]]; &mdash; applied both to officers and common mariners, but especially to the latter. Opposed to [[landman]] or [[landsman]].
#A particular rank for [[enlisted]] personnel in the US Navy and Coast Guard.
#A [[merman]]; the male of the [[mermaid]].
#:''Not to mention mermaids or seamen.'' &mdash; [[w:Locke|Locke]].

<!--put in separate entries
::{Able seaman}, a sailor who is practically conversant with all the duties of common seamanship.

